@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Barrzar" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
8 colours.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Barrzar runs fine
      on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with a
      68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any bar, this will 'invert' that bar from left
to right. If the inverted bar completes a series of bars that goes
from the upper part to the lower part of the game board, all bars
from that series will be highlighted, and they will be removed
afterwards.

  However, if the inverted bar does not result in creating a
complete series of bars, a new bar will randomly appear on the
board... Do not let the game board fill up completely as if that
happens, the game will be over.

  When a series of bars is completed, the game checks if there are
'parasite' links. These links are left or right neighbouring bars
that are linked by their lower ends to the bars that are part of a
completed series. In addition, the game checks if all bars in a
series are of the same colour, and this, regardless of the colours
of parasite links, if there are any...

  The base score you get for each complete series of bars is one
point. If a series does not contain any parasite links, the number
of points will be multiplied by 10. If the bars are all of the same
colour, the number of points will be multiplied by 100... so it is
possible to get up to 1000 points for any series of bars...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

